          "course_name": "Language Arts",
          "curriculum_blurb": "Language arts are interwoven throughout the fifth-grade curriculum. This fall, all students read In the Year of the Boar and Jackie Robinson, both at home and in school. Through class conversations and writing assignments, students were asked to describe character change over time using textual evidence. Students were also encouraged to reflect on an authors craft through their use of setting, figurative language, and theme.\r\n\r\nThe students were guided to elaborate their ideas, thoughts, and interpretations in well planned and well-organized paragraphs in response to what theyd read. Using checklists and graphic organizers, students learned to express their ideas clearly, to revise their work, to develop editing skills, and to improve their mechanics. \r\n\r\nOur spelling study focused on prefixes, suffixes, and roots. Each week, students studied a particular spelling pattern and were encouraged to use their knowledge of spelling patterns to learn the context of new vocabulary and apply these in their own daily writing.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
