          "curriculum_blurb": "Our fall Social Studies unit focuses on the study of Human Rights. Students are asked to consider what it means to have rights and what rights should be guaranteed to all humans. Students are introduced to the United Nations Declaration of Human Rights and learn about how and why the document came to be written. Through reading news articles and watching videos, students explore how human rights are granted, the challenges they face, and and how they are enforced. They also study the impact our changing climate has on these rights. In class discussions and written paragraphs, students consider the importance of human rights, the challenges people face in obtaining rights, and the ways people work for change to ensure equal rights for all. \r\n",
